<div id="review_775381905" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/775381905" />
    <a title="Tina " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5009669-tina"><img alt="Tina " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1621921610p2/5009669.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/775381905?book_show_action=true">Nov 27, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tina " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tina " href="/user/show/5009669-tina">Tina </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5009669-tina?shelf=books-made-into-movies-or-tv-shows">books-made-into-movies-or-tv-shows</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer775381905" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5630386277160468721">This is a hard one for me to rate. I didn&apos;t love the book but I liked the idea around it. At times it dragged and other times I was very engaged. It took me awhile to get into all 5 stories but when I did I was totally immersed in them. I think this will definitely make a good movie. Although, it may just be one of those minority books where the movie is better.</span>
  <span id="freeText5630386277160468721" style="display:none">This is a hard one for me to rate. I didn't love the book but I liked the idea around it. At times it dragged and other times I was very engaged. It took me awhile to get into all 5 stories but when I did I was totally immersed in them. I think this will definitely make a good movie. Although, it may just be one of those minority books where the movie is better.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5630386277160468721" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


